   <abstract>Beauford Delaney sketchbook circa 1950s. Contains daily to-do lists, appointment reminders, and drafted correspondence. Beauford Delaney mentions beginning to read Tropic of Cancer by Henry Miller. Contains notable ink sketches of Duke Ellington playing the piano and a portrait of Henry Miller.</abstract>
   <note>Brown spiral, 'Tropic of Cancer' written across front.</note>
   <note>Ink, graphite, watercolor.</note>
